Parliament, Monday, 12 March 2018 – The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) will tomorrow be briefed by the Directorate for Priority Crime Investigation (Hawks) on cases currently being handled. Details of meeting: Date: Tuesday, 13 March 2018
	Time: 09:00
	Venue: V454, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building Meanwhile in the evening, Scopa will be briefed by the Inter-Ministerial Committee (IMC) on the South African Social Security Agency (Sassa) and the South African Post Office (Sapo) repayment. Details of meeting: Date: Tuesday, 13 March 2018
	Time: 18:00
	Venue: V454, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF SCOPA, MR THEMBA GODI For media inquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Media Officer: Name: Ms Faith Ndenze
